avdta.network.node

Class Diverge

  • java.lang.Object
    • avdta.network.node.IntersectionControl
      • avdta.network.node.Diverge

  • public class Diverge
extends IntersectionControl
    This class implements the diverge intersection control at a node.
    A diverge is an intersection with an incoming link to a node and more than one outgoing links from the node.
    movements maps a link to a PhaseMovement through HashMap.
    See Also:
    IntersectionControl

      • calculateFlow

        public void calculateFlow(java.util.List<Vehicle> sendingFlow)
        Calculates the flows to be moved.
        Starts a new time-step for each of the outgoing links which involves reseting flow variables to zero after calculating the leftovers and also notes the receiving flow for each of the outgoing links.
        Checks for each vehicle in sendingFlow if the current node is the destination, if not then vehicle count is added to sending FLow S.
        Find the proportion of the sending flow phi which is leaving the upstream link.
        Once the proportion is known the flows can be calculated.
        Adds leftovers (from the previous time-step) of the outgoing flows to their flows in the next step.
        Parameters:
        sendingFlow - List of vehicles which can be sent in the current time-step.

      • step

        public int step()
        Implement movements at a diverge for a time-step.
        exited is for counting the number of vehicles that have exited the link.
        Gets vehicles on the incoming link of the diverge to find the sending flow. Calculates the flow variables for the sending array list using calculateFlow(sending).
        For each of the vehicle in the array list check the next link for them in the route, if the current link is the last link exit them and update the exited count (also records the simulator time: exit_time = Simulator.time;}) else calculates the equivalent flow of the vehicle and if there is available capacity then move the vehicle to the next link (removing the vehicle from the incoming link to the outgoing link links of the diverge node) and update the left flow of the phase movement of the link and also the receiving flow of the next link.
        Specified by:
        step in class IntersectionControl
        Returns:
        Returns the number of vehicle which has exited the network.
